data.text:
Made the Athletic Director’s Honor Roll for the Fall 2023 semester

2023 (Fr.): Redshirted and did not see any action…Played for the Ocean State Waves in the New England Collegiate Baseball League…Went 5x14 (.357) in 14 games with the Waves with a double and three RBI…Also pitched in 10 games during the regular season and did not post a record over 12 innings of work

A member of the Fall 2022 semester Athletic Director’s Honor Roll.

High School: A first-team Class 6A All-State selection at Madison Central High School…Earned All-Metro by MSScoreboard.com and all-district honors as well his senior season…Team finished 20-9 his last year, getting to the second round of the state playoffs…Batted .477 with 42 runs, three doubles, three triples and 27 RBI to help lead his school to a 34-2 record as a junior and the Class 6A state championship…A National High School Baseball Coaches Association Academic All-American…Was named Mr. Madison Central for the Class of 2022, as well as Most Athletic at the school.

Personal: Son of Scott and Mindi Cook…Born July 13…Majoring in Biomedical Science.
